'''cdrdao''' is [[open source software]] for [[authoring]] and [[ripping]] of [[CD-ROM]]s. The software is released under the [[GNU General Public License|GPL]]. Cdrdao records audio or data [[CD-R]]s in [[Disk-At-Once]] mode based on a textual description of the CD contents. The ''cdrdao'' program is run from the [[command line]] and has no [[graphical user interface]], except for third-party ones such as [[K3b]].
